WEBVTT

00:01.036 --> 00:02.891
In the criminal justice system

00:02.956 --> 00:06.371
sexually-based offenses are
considered especially heinous.

00:06.444 --> 00:08.833
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives...

00:08.908 --> 00:10.597
who investigate these vicious felonies

00:10.667 --> 00:13.863
are members of an elite squad
known as the Special Victims Unit.

00:13.931 --> 00:15.273
These are their stories.

00:22.890 --> 00:26.120
Miss Owens? It's Jimmy.

00:32.459 --> 00:33.570
Hello?

00:37.641 --> 00:39.681
I'm here to fix the toilet.

00:41.000 --> 00:47.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:50.282 --> 00:51.623
Miss Owens?

00:55.946 --> 00:57.636
Mary, Mother of God.

01:01.929 --> 01:03.173
Who turned on the radio?

01:03.241 --> 01:05.031
It was on when she was found.

01:05.098 --> 01:06.592
Okay. And she is?

01:06.666 --> 01:08.738
Marnie Owens, age 37,
lived alone.

01:08.809 --> 01:10.271
The doc says
she was probably raped.

01:10.345 --> 01:12.254
The door doesn't look
like it was forced open.

01:12.330 --> 01:13.758
Yeah.
The lock worked this morning.

01:13.833 --> 01:15.175
That's the super.
He found her.

01:15.241 --> 01:16.451
Kill the radio.

01:17.770 --> 01:19.679
I came to fix the toilet.

01:20.297 --> 01:21.475
She call you?

01:21.544 --> 01:24.392
Last night. She said
it was keeping her awake.

01:25.065 --> 01:28.065
Then the boiler goes out.
I had to fix the heat first.

01:28.137 --> 01:29.860
Told her I'd be here today.

01:30.183 --> 01:31.559
Bedroom door open or closed?

01:31.625 --> 01:32.551
Closed.

01:32.616 --> 01:36.446
I heard music playing, like maybe she
slept through the alarm or something.

01:36.520 --> 01:40.547
I figured I better knock on it, you know,
in case I walked in on her undressed.

01:40.648 --> 01:42.174
Detectives.

01:42.697 --> 01:43.679
Give us a minute.

01:43.752 --> 01:45.410
I'm not going nowhere.

01:47.081 --> 01:49.862
Fluids and bruising
around the genitals.

01:50.344 --> 01:51.837
Cause of death?

01:51.911 --> 01:53.504
Manual strangulation.

01:54.216 --> 01:57.478
Bruising around the neck,
petechial hemorrhaging.

01:57.544 --> 01:59.615
Dead about 10, 12 hours.

01:59.687 --> 02:00.635
She put up a fight.

02:00.711 --> 02:02.654
You get anything from
underneath the fingernails?

02:02.727 --> 02:04.069
Nothing I can see.

02:04.391 --> 02:06.464
We'll know more
after the autopsy.

02:10.632 --> 02:12.225
Don't pick it up.

02:14.086 --> 02:15.265
Elliot.

02:16.551 --> 02:19.105
This is Marnie.
You know the drill.

02:20.294 --> 02:23.491
Marnie, it's Ruth. It's 10:00.
We're starting to worry.

02:23.624 --> 02:25.630
Please call as soon
as you get this. Bye.

02:25.702 --> 02:27.612
Caller ID says
New York City schools.

02:27.686 --> 02:28.766
Olivia.

02:39.975 --> 02:41.436
Her wall of fame.

02:42.181 --> 02:44.800
Outstanding teacher, 1998.

02:46.981 --> 02:48.388
School's out.

03:35.149 --> 03:39.110
So, Marnie Owens survives a tour of duty
in one of the city's worst high schools...

03:39.180 --> 03:40.806
but she isn't safe
in her own apartment.

03:40.875 --> 03:43.363
No doorman. All the doer
had to do was follow her in.

03:43.436 --> 03:45.858
Or be invited. No forced
entry into her apartment.

03:45.931 --> 03:48.037
If she had one, there were
no pictures. A boyfriend?

03:48.108 --> 03:49.701
Plenty of pictures
of students, though.

03:49.771 --> 03:51.681
Her dining room,
set up like a mini classroom.

03:51.756 --> 03:53.479
She seemed
like a very dedicated teacher.

03:53.547 --> 03:55.402
So we can't
rule out a student.

03:55.467 --> 03:56.514
What'd CSU turn up?

03:56.587 --> 03:59.271
Traces of semen on the bed and
two different colors of hair...

03:59.340 --> 04:00.354
one matching the victim's.

04:00.427 --> 04:02.499
Guy who found her,
building super.

04:02.572 --> 04:04.294
Record's clean, alibi checks.

04:04.363 --> 04:06.371
Also found a half-empty bottle
of Prozac.

04:06.442 --> 04:08.809
We had her job,
we might all be depressed.

04:08.876 --> 04:10.282
Any therapy appointments
in there?

04:10.348 --> 04:11.656
No. Just tutoring sessions.

04:11.723 --> 04:15.236
Last one was with Ethan
Chance, last night, 6:00.

04:15.531 --> 04:17.897
You two, go over
to Owens' school, all right?

04:17.962 --> 04:21.637
See if one of her hard case students
was giving her more trouble than usual.

04:22.283 --> 04:24.552
Poor Munch and Fin
get to canvas in the cold.

04:28.491 --> 04:30.115
Marnie was special.

04:30.186 --> 04:32.521
The kind of teacher
I'd like to clone.

04:33.355 --> 04:36.201
She took 10th graders reading
at a third grade level...

04:36.267 --> 04:39.528
and got them through Regents
Exam and into college.

04:40.074 --> 04:42.921
Her most challenging students
she tutored at home.

04:42.986 --> 04:43.848
No charge.

04:43.914 --> 04:44.864
That's dedication.

04:44.937 --> 04:47.459
Takes creativity to
motivate kids like that.

04:47.594 --> 04:49.481
Marnie did things like...

04:49.546 --> 04:53.190
having her seniors write plays
about their lives.

04:54.729 --> 04:58.374
Marnie helped them articulate
their fears and dreams.

04:58.442 --> 05:00.132
What about
her personal life?

05:00.201 --> 05:01.957
I'm surprised she had one.

05:02.217 --> 05:06.047
We were friends here, but Marnie never
shared much about her life outside.

05:06.312 --> 05:07.687
Did she seem depressed?

05:07.754 --> 05:08.736
No.

05:09.128 --> 05:12.260
She missed a meeting on Friday.
First time in five years.

05:12.329 --> 05:16.323
I asked her if anything was wrong. She
said it was nothing she couldn't handle.

05:16.393 --> 05:18.662
In her lesson planner,
she had a tutoring session...

05:18.728 --> 05:20.735
scheduled with
an Ethan Chance?

05:20.808 --> 05:22.052
One of her prodigies.

05:22.120 --> 05:24.608
Kid from a drug corner, has
a real shot at college now.

05:24.680 --> 05:26.590
We'll need to talk to him.

05:28.200 --> 05:29.794
This was Marnie's room.

05:31.305 --> 05:32.865
I'll get Ethan for you.

05:40.807 --> 05:42.369
You cops?

05:42.439 --> 05:43.454
Yes.

05:45.159 --> 05:48.159
My little girl is gonna
graduate because of Miss Owens.

05:49.159 --> 05:50.785
We're sorry for your loss.

05:51.015 --> 05:52.837
It's not just my loss.

05:53.064 --> 05:54.755
Look at these kids.

05:56.519 --> 05:58.374
Please find the man
that did this to us.

05:58.439 --> 06:00.227
We're doing everything we can.

06:03.975 --> 06:05.121
Excuse me.

06:05.191 --> 06:07.133
Ethan never showed up
for school this morning.

06:07.207 --> 06:08.800
We'll need his address.
Of course.

06:08.872 --> 06:09.886
Do you know
his parents?

06:09.958 --> 06:13.220
No father. Mother's a teller at
a bank on Canal and Lafayette.

06:15.143 --> 06:16.866
I thought he went
to school early.

06:16.934 --> 06:18.756
Principal said
he never showed up.

06:18.823 --> 06:21.757
Damn that boy. Miss Owens
is not gonna tolerate that.

06:23.143 --> 06:24.834
Miss Owens was murdered.

06:25.447 --> 06:26.940
Oh, dear God. No.

06:27.015 --> 06:29.086
Ethan had a tutoring session
with her last night.

06:29.158 --> 06:30.816
We thought he might
be able to help us.

06:30.885 --> 06:33.373
I owe her a lot.
She turned Ethan around.

06:33.447 --> 06:36.927
Showed him there were other possibilities
besides slinging dope on some corner.

06:36.997 --> 06:39.616
I told Ethan,
I don't visit nobody in jail.

06:39.686 --> 06:41.345
What time did he come home last night?

06:41.414 --> 06:43.803
Around 11:00. On school
nights, that's his...

06:44.165 --> 06:45.114
No.

06:45.190 --> 06:47.491
He's been in trouble for drugs,
but he's straightened out.

06:47.557 --> 06:49.052
He's a good boy.

06:49.125 --> 06:51.547
Did Ethan say anything
about his tutoring session?

06:52.230 --> 06:54.139
He just said
Miss Owens yelled at him.

06:54.213 --> 06:57.891
I asked him why, he runs into
his room and slams the door.

06:58.181 --> 06:59.675
I wake up this morning
and he's gone.

06:59.749 --> 07:00.862
Any idea where?

07:02.213 --> 07:05.725
When he cut school, he used to hang
out on the corner with some losers.

07:05.861 --> 07:07.291
Suffolk and Rivington.

07:08.389 --> 07:10.276
She lived next door
for six years.

07:10.821 --> 07:14.814
Came to visit me at the rehab
hospital after I fell last year.

07:14.884 --> 07:15.964
You knew her well?

07:16.037 --> 07:18.623
She was
such a nice girl.

07:19.109 --> 07:22.175
Not like that other one,
down the hall. That kurva.

07:22.245 --> 07:23.521
Yiddish for whore.

07:23.588 --> 07:26.458
Did you notice anybody come in or
out of Marnie's apartment last night?

07:27.364 --> 07:29.632
Well, one of her students.

07:29.860 --> 07:32.249
Yeah. He went in
around suppertime.

07:32.965 --> 07:34.044
Looked like a hood.

07:34.117 --> 07:35.490
Can you describe him?

07:35.555 --> 07:37.214
He was a Black kid.

07:37.509 --> 07:40.126
Wearing a kind
of a brown jacket.

07:40.195 --> 07:41.570
You hear anything?

07:41.636 --> 07:44.091
Some loud voices
while I was eating.

07:44.164 --> 07:45.374
What were they saying?

07:45.444 --> 07:47.713
My hearing is
as old as I am, Officer.

07:48.130 --> 07:52.408
My son had to buy me special headphones
for the TV just to hear my Rosie.

07:52.675 --> 07:54.562
Did you know any
of Marnie's boyfriends?

07:54.628 --> 07:56.122
What boyfriends?

07:56.579 --> 07:59.546
The only one I ever saw
was... What was his name?

08:00.067 --> 08:02.336
Byron. A doctor, no less.

08:02.852 --> 08:04.674
But he hasn't come around
for a while.

08:04.739 --> 08:05.884
What about family?

08:05.955 --> 08:07.930
Her parents passed away.

08:08.003 --> 08:10.392
All she had left
was her brother, Jordan.

08:10.627 --> 08:12.700
But I haven't seen him
for years.

08:17.571 --> 08:18.912
It's her.

08:21.538 --> 08:22.684
My God.

08:24.258 --> 08:26.909
Now I told her not to live in
a building without a doorman.

08:26.979 --> 08:28.385
We need to ask you
a few questions.

08:28.450 --> 08:29.431
Can't it wait?

08:29.506 --> 08:31.067
I understand
you're distraught.

08:31.138 --> 08:32.894
Just one question.

08:33.282 --> 08:35.866
Marnie's neighbor mentioned
a boyfriend, some doctor.

08:35.938 --> 08:38.687
Boyfriend. Try affair.
He was married.

08:39.682 --> 08:41.570
This affair have a name?

08:42.370 --> 08:43.897
Byron Marks.

08:43.969 --> 08:45.628
Surgeon over at Bellevue.

08:46.754 --> 08:49.536
I told her to stay away
from a married guy.

08:52.865 --> 08:54.175
We ain't doing nothing.

08:54.241 --> 08:55.769
Hi. You guys
seen Ethan around?

08:55.874 --> 08:57.084
Ethan Hawke?

08:57.152 --> 08:58.396
You got
the wrong 'hood, man.

08:58.465 --> 08:59.675
Don't play us.

09:01.506 --> 09:02.880
You talking
about Little E?

09:03.777 --> 09:05.468
He's too good
for us now, right?

09:05.536 --> 09:07.958
Ever since he got
his "edumacation."

09:08.033 --> 09:10.750
Is there some kind of school
holiday I don't know about?

09:10.817 --> 09:11.962
I got the flu.

09:12.033 --> 09:13.342
Yeah? What about you?

09:14.465 --> 09:15.741
It's contagious.

09:15.809 --> 09:17.532
We're gonna ask you
one more time.

09:17.601 --> 09:19.903
We don't like the answer,
we're gonna play show-and-tell.

09:19.969 --> 09:22.172
You want us to go
through your pockets?

09:22.656 --> 09:24.445
We don't look good
talking to y'all.

09:24.513 --> 09:26.749
Yeah, we told y'all.
What's up with this?

09:27.553 --> 09:28.413
Okay.

09:28.480 --> 09:32.091
Look. Yo, last night he was talking about
that teacher of his. He was down about it.

09:32.993 --> 09:34.039
Where was that?

09:34.113 --> 09:34.973
Schoolyard.

09:35.039 --> 09:36.152
What time?

09:36.224 --> 09:37.685
I don't know.
I don't got a watch.

09:37.760 --> 09:38.775
Yeah? What did he say?

09:38.848 --> 09:40.408
He was riled up about it.

09:40.480 --> 09:41.407
Why?

09:41.472 --> 09:42.813
They had some type of fight.

09:42.879 --> 09:44.057
What'd he say
about the fight?

09:44.128 --> 09:45.535
Ain't say nothing
about the fight.

09:45.599 --> 09:48.894
He just said he had to go home before
his mother came looking for him.

09:53.056 --> 09:55.706
I was separated.
I wouldn't call it an affair.

09:55.775 --> 09:58.492
Was Marnie the reason
you and your wife split?

09:59.902 --> 10:02.804
That was coming long before
I knew Marnie.

10:02.878 --> 10:04.155
How long did you two
go out?

10:04.224 --> 10:07.256
About a half a year. We met in a
mentoring program for inner-city kids.

10:07.326 --> 10:08.701
When's the last time
you saw her?

10:08.767 --> 10:10.555
The night we broke up.
Three months ago.

10:10.623 --> 10:11.605
What happened?

10:11.678 --> 10:13.467
I was looking
for a relationship.

10:13.535 --> 10:14.877
She wasn't.

10:14.943 --> 10:17.529
My experience is usually
the other way around.

10:17.599 --> 10:20.281
I'm a nester. I was more than
ready to settle down with Marnie.

10:20.351 --> 10:22.718
But the only commitment
she wanted was with her kids.

10:22.783 --> 10:24.027
We have to ask.

10:24.094 --> 10:26.233
Where were you last night
around 10:00?

10:26.878 --> 10:30.937
I was at dinner with my new girlfriend.
Spent the night at her apartment.

10:31.006 --> 10:32.414
She a nester?

10:33.694 --> 10:35.101
Just like me.

10:35.869 --> 10:39.098
I looked everywhere, called
everyone I know, all his friends.

10:39.166 --> 10:40.824
What else can I do?

10:41.150 --> 10:44.248
Well, would you mind if we
took a look around Ethan's room?

10:45.021 --> 10:46.777
It's that door right there.

10:50.813 --> 10:53.082
Your kids keep their rooms
this clean?

10:54.142 --> 10:55.253
I wish.

10:55.324 --> 10:56.819
Ethan's into sports.

10:56.893 --> 10:59.161
I make sure his schoolwork
comes first.

11:03.805 --> 11:04.950
Olivia.

11:09.565 --> 11:12.631
Looks like Miss Owens was teaching
her students more than just English.

11:12.701 --> 11:14.108
Facts of life.
What?

11:16.029 --> 11:18.647
Good lord.
What was she doing to my son?

11:19.452 --> 11:21.460
Ethan's mother doesn't know
what he was wearing...

11:21.533 --> 11:23.256
except that
his brown parka's missing.

11:23.324 --> 11:24.884
We thinking
he's the teacher's pet?

11:24.957 --> 11:26.363
The teacher
doing the petting.

11:26.429 --> 11:28.796
She seduces him, gets what
she wants, then dumps him.

11:28.860 --> 11:30.551
Teenage hormones
plus jealousy and rage?

11:30.620 --> 11:33.238
I'd call that a potentially
deadly combination.

11:33.596 --> 11:36.465
This picture didn't get
on the Internet by accident.

11:36.540 --> 11:38.744
Get Marnie's PC down
to computer crimes...

11:38.812 --> 11:41.911
find out what and who else
might be on that hard drive.

11:41.980 --> 11:43.321
The ex's story track?

11:43.388 --> 11:45.908
Said he was in the sack with
his latest squeeze Sunday night.

11:45.979 --> 11:47.223
We're still trying
to reach her.

11:47.292 --> 11:48.307
What about the funeral?

11:48.379 --> 11:50.713
Private. School's sponsoring
a memorial service tomorrow.

11:50.780 --> 11:54.936
You know, Ethan's probably feeling
guilty. Remorseful. He could be there.

11:55.355 --> 11:58.703
All right. We'll have a detail
outside the church, just in case he is.

11:58.780 --> 12:01.714
But for now don't rule out
any other possibilities.

12:01.787 --> 12:03.696
Photo unit will be there as well.

12:20.891 --> 12:22.962
Four of us
and hundreds of them?

12:23.066 --> 12:24.725
What, you don't like
those odds?

12:25.305 --> 12:27.061
Sounds like lottery odds
to me.

12:27.129 --> 12:28.690
Least this is almost over.

12:45.658 --> 12:48.757
I got a brown jacket heading
west toward the church.

12:52.666 --> 12:53.942
I see him.

13:00.793 --> 13:02.003
Negative.

13:05.528 --> 13:08.311
I got another one. Brown parka.
Heading east towards the church.

13:08.377 --> 13:10.165
Hood's up. Can't see the face.

13:12.600 --> 13:14.291
Him. Zoom in on him.

13:17.273 --> 13:18.995
It's him. Fin,
he's coming right at you.

13:19.448 --> 13:20.463
I got him.

13:42.807 --> 13:43.790
Move!

14:09.687 --> 14:11.575
Making me run on my bad knee.

14:11.639 --> 14:12.621
I didn't do anything.

14:12.694 --> 14:14.004
Your mother's
looking for you.

14:14.071 --> 14:15.412
You're under arrest.

14:15.479 --> 14:17.201
You have the right
to remain silent.

14:17.270 --> 14:18.285
You give up that right...

14:18.358 --> 14:21.041
anything you say can and will be
used against you in a court of law.

14:21.110 --> 14:22.484
You have the right
to an attorney.

14:22.551 --> 14:25.070
If you can't afford one,
one will be appointed for you.

14:29.622 --> 14:31.116
Why'd you run?

14:36.150 --> 14:37.644
We found this
in your room.

14:37.718 --> 14:39.441
You want to explain it
to us?

14:40.981 --> 14:43.828
When did you and Miss Owens
start knocking boots?

14:44.500 --> 14:45.394
What?

14:45.461 --> 14:48.756
Come on, a hot teacher like her, she
comes onto you, you get something going...

14:48.822 --> 14:50.098
then she wants to turn it off. No!

14:50.165 --> 14:51.375
You couldn't stand it.

14:51.446 --> 14:53.900
But you couldn't stay away,
so what do you do?

14:53.973 --> 14:55.664
You show up to her service.

14:55.734 --> 14:56.943
I felt bad.

14:57.717 --> 15:00.335
I felt bad because
the last time I saw her...

15:01.237 --> 15:02.480
I called her a whore.

15:02.549 --> 15:03.977
'Cause she dumped you.

15:05.045 --> 15:06.605
Y'all got it all wrong, man!

15:06.677 --> 15:08.433
So tell us what's right.

15:14.229 --> 15:15.243
Come here.

15:17.140 --> 15:19.311
You were the last person
seen with her...

15:19.381 --> 15:20.657
you got this picture...

15:20.724 --> 15:22.219
okay, you're on the run.

15:22.292 --> 15:23.983
They line up
the dogs, man.

15:24.052 --> 15:27.914
If you don't give us something right
away, they're gonna turn the dogs loose.

15:31.187 --> 15:32.562
Little Camp gave me
that picture.

15:32.628 --> 15:34.035
What's his real name?

15:35.156 --> 15:36.268
Marcus Cole.

15:37.748 --> 15:41.229
Fool said he found it messing around
on some porn site on the Internet.

15:41.588 --> 15:44.076
She was advertising for guys
to have sex with her.

15:44.915 --> 15:48.461
Marcus said he was gonna spread that
picture around school to everybody.

15:48.819 --> 15:50.314
Why would he
want to do that?

15:50.963 --> 15:53.265
'Cause Miss Owens was
on his case about...

15:53.523 --> 15:55.213
not doing his work...

15:55.571 --> 15:57.033
cutting class.

15:58.418 --> 16:00.971
Tell us what happened
at the tutoring session?

16:04.786 --> 16:06.729
I showed her the picture.

16:10.931 --> 16:13.712
I tried to warn her about
what Marcus was gonna do.

16:14.578 --> 16:17.895
And she starts yelling. Yelling at
me like it's my fault or something.

16:19.794 --> 16:21.288
She tells me to get out.

16:21.810 --> 16:23.850
Well, that must have
made you angry.

16:25.138 --> 16:27.178
Look, I didn't
do anything, man.

16:28.370 --> 16:30.312
I did nothing.
I was just trying to help her.

16:30.386 --> 16:31.564
You disappeared.

16:31.634 --> 16:34.667
I went back to apologize the
next morning before school...

16:37.585 --> 16:40.072
and I get to her building
and you all were there.

16:40.977 --> 16:44.294
So I asked some guy in the crowd,
what's going on and he says...

16:48.849 --> 16:50.703
He says a woman
was murdered...

16:53.073 --> 16:54.502
on the third floor.

16:56.113 --> 16:58.285
Miss Owens lived
on the third floor.

17:02.608 --> 17:04.943
