that time by the police and the killer.

36:20.650 --> 36:22.144
I hope that
you will consider...

36:26.506 --> 36:27.815
Excuse me.

36:31.369 --> 36:32.318
What's going on here?

36:32.392 --> 36:34.248
My client wishes
to exercise his right...

36:34.312 --> 36:35.873
to make a statement
to the grand jury.

36:35.945 --> 36:36.839
Too late.

36:36.904 --> 36:37.985
They haven't voted.

36:38.056 --> 36:40.161
I know what you're trying
to do and it won't work.

36:40.233 --> 36:43.081
Well, you got to play to win.
Let's see what a judge decides.

36:49.032 --> 36:53.505
190.50 of the CPL states that notice
must be filed in a timely fashion.

36:53.576 --> 36:54.624
Read the statute.

36:54.697 --> 36:58.242
It says the defendant can appear as long
as the indictment has not been filed.

36:58.311 --> 36:59.555
They haven't even voted yet.

36:59.624 --> 37:02.210
You told me yesterday your
client declined to testify.

37:02.280 --> 37:04.865
Well, he's changed his mind.
He has that right.

37:04.936 --> 37:08.383
